  "What does the Second Derivative Test state?": "",
  "If f'(c) = 0, then c is always an extremum": "",
  "If f'(c)=0 and f''(c)>0, then c is a local min; if f''(c)<0, then c is a local max; if f''(c)=0, inconclusive": "",
  "The test determines concavity of the entire function": "",
  "If f''(c) = 0, then c is an inflection point": "",
  "The Second Derivative Test: at a critical point c where f'(c)=0, if f''(c)>0 it's a local min (concave up), if f''(c)<0 it's a local max (concave down), if f''(c)=0 the test gives no conclusion.": "",
  "When is the Second Derivative Test 'inconclusive'?": "",
  "When f'(c) does not exist": "",
  "When the function is not continuous": "",
  "When f''(c) > 0": "",
  "When f''(c) = 0 at the critical point": "",
