  "The graph is concave down at c": "",
  "The graph is concave up at c, forming a valley (local minimum)": "",
  "The function is increasing at c": "",
  "f''(c) > 0 means concave up at c. Combined with f'(c) = 0 (horizontal tangent), this creates a valley shape: a local minimum.": "",
  "What is the advantage of the Second Derivative Test over the First Derivative Test?": "",
  "It always works": "",
  "It is more accurate": "",
  "It finds inflection points simultaneously": "",
  "It can classify critical points without checking intervals on either side": "",
  "The Second Derivative Test only requires evaluating f'' at the critical point, without needing to check the sign of f' on intervals to the left and right.": "",
